      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_04_page02.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <salute>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">
                     Dear Madam,<!-- Use if letter has a saluation ("Dear Sir," for example). If not, delete this line.-->
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
                One little commission<lb/>
                more I must trouble<lb/>
                you with to get me<lb/>
                3 yards of trimming<lb/>
                nearly to match the<lb/>
                enclosed -. You need<lb/>
                not be very exact -<lb/>
                This I think may be<lb/>
                ventured between the<lb/>
                leaves of the next proof<lb/>
                of <title ref="./Workography.xml#Harry1">Harry &amp; Lucy</title> wrapped<lb/>
                in silver paper <lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_04_page03.jpg"/>
            <p>send between the leaves<lb/>
                of these books any little<lb/>
                articles you have for me<lb/>
                &amp; I should be much obliged<lb/>
                to you if you would add<lb/>
                3 yards of nett about<lb/>
                this breadth<lb/>
                and 18 &amp; 1/2 yard valencienne<lb/>
                edgings about this<lb/>
                breadth<lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_04_page04.jpg"/>
            <p>I hope your little ones<lb/>
                are well &amp; I wish you<lb/>
                would mention them<lb/>
                when you write - I hope<lb/>
                also that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">
                  M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> has<lb/>
                quite left off tumbling<lb/>
                from gigs or horses?<lb/>
                My father is perfectly <choice>
                  <orig>re<lb/>
                established</orig>
                  <reg>re-established</reg>
               </choice> thank God -<lb/>
                My brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL2">Lovell</persName> much<lb/>
                better - he sailed last night<lb/>
                for <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#ENK">England</placeName> - Whether he<lb/>
                goes to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Bath_ENK">Bath</placeName> or <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> first<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><!--More body paragraphs as needed.--></p>
            <closer>
               Y<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> truly
                <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <address>
                  <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_unknown_04_page01.jpg"/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
